This article is a transcript of remarks made by President Obama at the home of Sergeant First Class Cory Remsburg in Gilbert, Arizona. The President expresses his admiration for Cory and the inspirational relationship they have developed. He discusses Cory's service and the injuries he sustained defending the country. The President also praises Cory's positive attitude and determination. He acknowledges the efforts of Cory's family, the community, and various organizations in supporting him. The President emphasizes the importance of taking care of veterans and acknowledges that not all wounds are visible. He concludes by thanking Cory and expressing his pride in him.